<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 6:31PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Tazewell and southwestern Mercer Counties through 700 PM EDT...
At 631 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boissevain, or near Bluefield, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bluefield...
Pocahontas...
Bramwell...
Coaldale...
Tiptop...
Pinnacle Rock State Park...
and Boissevain.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
